Biography

Career: Scored three goals, two assists for eight points in 35 matches played, 25 starts … Has two career three-point games, one against VMI and one against Campbell … Has 26 total shots, 10 on target … Has played 1955 minutes in career.

2017 (Senior): Played 16 matches with 13 starts, tallying one goal and an assist for three points … Recorded 13 shots, two on target … Played 953 minutes … Tallied season-high 83 minutes against James Madison … Registered goal and an assist against Campbell to match career-high three points.

2016 (Junior): Played 19 matches with 12 starts, tallying two goals and an assist for five points … Recorded 12 shots, eight on target … Played 1002 minutes … Tallied season-best three points in Longwood debut at VMI, notching a goal and an assist … Also, scored a goal against Campbell.

2015 (Lander University): Started three of 14 matches, scoring one goal...registered four shots, including four on goal...scored the game-winner in a 6-1 blowout against North Greenville (Sept. 16).

2014 (Lander University): Appeared in all 14 matches, making nine starts...recorded five points on two goals and one assist... Registered 13 shots on the year...netted first career goal in 3-0 win over North Greenville (Sept. 10)...posted first career assist in 3-3 draw against Georgia Southwestern (Sept. 20)...scored in 3-2 loss to USC Aiken (Oct. 1).

Personal: Son of Gerard and Joan O Donovan…youngest of four siblings…aspires to play pro or semipro soccer upon graduation from college.
